<subSubSection id="C358655E861D6B3BFED58DE1FEDFFD65" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED58DE1FEDFFD65" blockId="15.[219,1202,405,766]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Remarks. The structure of the submerged protoconch of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BFECF8DB7FE41FE71" authorityName="Holzapfel" authorityYear="1889" box="[279,475,451,490]" class="Gastropoda" family="Porcelliidae" genus="Hesperiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BFECF8DB7FE41FE71" box="[279,475,451,490]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Hesperiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24861D6B3BFC738DB7FB30FE71" author="Knight, J. B." box="[939,1194,451,490]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" refId="ref26100" refString="Knight, J. B., 1941. Paleozoic gastropod genotypes. Geological Society of America, Special papers 32, 510 pp. 32 figs, 96 pIs." type="book" year="1941">Knight (1941)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24861D6B3BFF048D85FE50FD83" author="Batten, R. L." box="[220,458,497,536]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" pagination="53 - 109" refId="ref24332" refString="Batten, R. L., 1966. The Lower Carboniferous gastropod fauna from the Hotwells Limestone of Compton Martin, Somerset. Palaeontographical Society Monographs, London Pt I: 152, pis 15; Pt 1 I: 53 - 109, pis 6 - 10." type="journal article" year="1966">Batten (1966)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24861D6B3BFDF78D85FD60FD83" author="Yoo, E. K." box="[559,762,497,536]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" pagination="233 - 264" refId="ref27552" refString="Yoo, E. K., 1988. Early Carboniferous Mollusca from Gundy, Upper Hunter, New South Wales. Records of the Australian Museum 40 (4): 233 - 264." type="journal article" year="1988">Yoo (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. It is almost certain that this genus has a hyperstrophically coiled dextral shell. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BFF038E39FE3AFDEF" authorityName="Holzapfel" authorityYear="1889" box="[219,416,589,628]" class="Gastropoda" family="Porcelliidae" genus="Hesperiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BFF038E39FE3AFDEF" box="[219,416,589,628]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Hesperiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow selenizone seen only in the final whorl. The slit is observed in the juvenile specimens (PI. 7 figs 10-12), although it is not obvious in the adult shells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
